Independence Township is a township in Doniphan County, Kansas, United States.  As of the 2020 census, its population was 257.
Geography
Independence Township covers an area of  and contains no incorporated settlements.
The streams of Jordan Creek and North Branch Independence Creek run through this township.
Demographics
As of the 2020 census, there were 257 people living in the township. The population density was . There were 129 housing units. The racial makeup of the township was 95.3% White alone, 0.4% Some Other Race alone, and 4.3% two or more races.
